            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13459",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "#2 is actually a result of PHP's round() failing to produce correct results. This test only fails on certain platforms, when the BCMath extension is not enabled.  We are not going to provide a workaround for PHP's round().  The recommended fix is to enable the BCMath extension.  I committed a change to prevent the failed test from running when BCMath is not enabled.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-17T21:34:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-17T21:34:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13461",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "#1 only occurs for me when I disabled BCMath.  Thomas committed a new version of the function involved (toNumber) and is working on it.\n\n{code}\n$ svn diff TestConfiguration.php.dist\nIndex: TestConfiguration.php.dist\n===================================================================\n--- TestConfiguration.php.dist  (revision 4087)\n+++ TestConfiguration.php.dist  (working copy)\n@@ -155,7 +155,7 @@\n  *\n  * Edit TestConfiguration.php, not TestConfiguration.php.dist.\n  *\/\n-define('TESTS_ZEND_LOCALE_BCMATH_ENABLED', true);\n+define('TESTS_ZEND_LOCALE_BCMATH_ENABLED', false);\n\n \/**\n  * Zend_Locale tests\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-17T22:12:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-17T22:12:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13472",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Than report that wrong behavior to php.net.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T03:46:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T03:46:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13481",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you for your understanding in our hard work.\n\nBut as we are not the developers of php itself we are also not able to fix such problems within the extensions.\nEven if the php developers can fix the problem in future versions of php it still remains in the actual version and therefor we would also have the problem within our framework.\n\nWe will see to find a workaround for the framework itself but not for the underlaying BCMath extension or our own BCMath extension class.\n\nSo please be pationed.\n\nBtw:\nThis problem is known since 2002 but has not been fixed until now.\nSee http:\/\/bugs.php.net\/bug.php?id=16532",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T05:52:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T05:52:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13486",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I was talking about the round issue. \n\n# First off all: You know about [http:\/\/docs.sun.com\/source\/806-3568\/ncg_goldberg.html]?\n# bcmath doesn't affect round() at all: [http:\/\/cvs.php.net\/viewvc.cgi\/php-src\/ext\/standard\/math.c?view=markup]. Nevertheless, I tried to reproduce it with PHP 5.2.1 bcmath enabled and bcmath disabled on various platforms:\n#* Happens on:\n#** Ubuntu Linux 2.6.15-26-686 (32bit on AMD Opteron(tm) Processor 146 - which is a 64 bit one):\\\\ 56055.1811\\\\ Note: Also happens with PHP_5_2 CVS, 5.2.0, 5.1.6, 5.1.5, 5.1.4 on the same machine\n#** On Ubuntu Linux 2.6.15-26-server (32bit on AMD Athlon(tm) Processor):\\\\ 56055.1811\\\\ Note: Also happens with 5.1.5 on the same machine.\n#** On Fedora Linux 2.6.9-1.667 SMP (32 bit on 2x Intel(R) Xeon(TM) CPU):\\\\ 56055.1811\n#** On Debian Linux 2.4.25 (32 bit on Intel(R) Celeron(R) CPU): \\\\ 56055.1811\n#* Does not happen on:\n#** CYGWIN_NT-5.1 1.5.24(0.156\/4\/2) (32 bit on Intel(R) Pentium(R) M processor):\\\\ 56055.1812\n#** On WinXP (32 bit on Intel(R) Pentium(R) M processor):\\\\ 56055.1812\n#** On Win2k (32 bit on Intel(R) Pentium(R) M processor):\\\\ 56055.1812\n\nWhat may lead you into the (in my eyes wrong assumption) that bcmath is the key is that windows builds have bcmath enabled by default, which Linux builds don't have.\n\nIf you have other platforms than Win32, where {{round(56055.18115, 4)}} is working mathematically correct, please provide details. Nevertheless, this is NOT a bug in PHP, the correct solution is testing this with a value that passes on all (or at least the most common) platforms.\n\nIf you still think, this is a bug in PHP, please prove that.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T07:29:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T07:29:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13488",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I say it once more again:\n\nPlease be patient, we will find a fix for the framework.\nSome issues can not be fixed within one day as we are working in our sparetime for the framework.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T09:46:23.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T09:46:23.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13489",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I don't want to hustle you. I just want to make clear, that Gavin's statement {quote}#2 is actually a result of PHP's round() failing to produce correct results. This test only fails on certain platforms, when the BCMath extension is not enabled. We are not going to provide a workaround for PHP's round(). The recommended fix is to enable the BCMath extension. I committed a change to prevent the failed test from running when BCMath is not enabled.{quote} is wrong in my eyes and that hiding the behaviour by disabling the tests when bcmath is not enabled is wrong as well.\n\nAnd of course I'd like to know anything that proves me wrong so that someone (Gavin, me, whoever else) can file a php.net bug in that case.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T10:01:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T10:01:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13492",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The first should now be fixed with SVN 4104.\nCould you please test it on your side ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T13:05:22.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T13:05:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13493",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Both work now.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T13:24:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T13:24:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13494",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm with gavin because the code is:\n\n{code}\n    public static function round($op1, $precision = 0)\n    {\n        if (self::$_bcmathDisabled) {\n            return (string) round($op1, $precision);\n        }\n    .....\n{code}\n\nSo... if BCMath is disabled it uses the standard php round function.\nAnd this produces a failure within linux environments because the lowest digit is truncated instead of rounded.\n\nCan you test something like this with disabled BCMath extension in Linux and Windows and give me the result ? \n\n{code}\nrequire_once('Zend\/Locale\/Format.php');\nprint \"\\n\".round(56055.18115, 4);\nprint \"\\n\".Zend_Locale_Math::round('56055.18115', 4);\n{code}\n\nShould output \"56055.1812\".\nIf seems that you have much more access to different OS types than myself ;-)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T13:25:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T13:25:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13495",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Nice... ;-)\n\nI didn't change anything with the second one... but I think it's becasue gavin changed the test behaviour.\nWith my short code you should be able to see if the problem is remaining or already gone ;-)\n\nAnyhow...\nI will close this issue as the original problem has been found.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-18T13:32:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T13:32:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13496",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with SVN 4104",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
