                    "created": "2007-03-18T13:33:29.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-18T13:33:29.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13508",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Changing fix version to 0.9.1.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
                        "name": "bkarwin",
                        "displayName": "Bill Karwin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-19T11:39:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-19T11:39:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13685",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "On Linux it's\n\n56055.1811\n56055.1811\n\nTesting without bcmath on windows is not that easy as bcmath is compiled into win32 builds and not a configurable extension.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-24T08:56:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-24T08:56:39.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13686",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It's already marked as fixed.\n\nAnyway, it seems that windows and linux don't behave the same way even with the standard round function from php...\n\nAnd as this is a problem from php itself we can not solve this...\nBecause mathematically \"round(56055.18115, 4);\" should output 56055.1812 and not .1811...\nand this is a php internal problem which the ZF can not solve.\n\nBut gavin pointed this already.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-03-24T11:23:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-03-24T11:23:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/13689",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Again: This is _not_ a bug in PHP: http:\/\/docs.sun.com\/source\/806-3568\/ncg_goldberg.html",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nohn",
                        "name": "nohn",
                        "displayName": "Sebastian Nohn",
                        "active": true
                    },
